.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-CONFIG" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.31" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-config \- Render the fully interpolated effective config
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose config [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Print the normalized effective compose config after interpolation, healthcheck normalization, and default application. Use this to inspect what plan, up, and inspect receive.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--variables\fR
Show resolved interpolation variables and their sources.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose config \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose config \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
